meanings: (복권 등의) a big[huge] win, (대성공) a great success, a big[great] hit
(exclamation) Dae-bak, a common term used to express approval or admiration for something. Similar to “cool” or “awesome”, it can be used flexibly as a noun or adverb.
make a pile of money on horseracing
